‚úÖ 1. CI/CD Pipeline with Jenkins + AWS (EC2 + S3)
Project Name: ci-cd-pipeline-jenkins-aws

Overview:

Set up Jenkins on an EC2 instance.

Trigger builds on code push from GitHub.

Build a sample Node.js/React app.

Store build artifacts in an S3 bucket.

Tech Stack:

Jenkins, AWS EC2, S3, GitHub, Bash, Node.js

Skills Demonstrated:

Jenkins Job Configuration

GitHub Webhook Integration

Artifact Management with S3

Bash Scripting for automation

Bonus: Add a Jenkinsfile for pipeline-as-code.

‚úÖ 2. Dockerized Web App Deployment using ECS (Fargate)
Project Name: docker-ecs-deployment

Overview:

Create a simple Flask or Node.js app.

Dockerize it.

Push the image to AWS ECR.

Deploy on AWS ECS (Fargate) using Task Definitions and Service.

Tech Stack:

Docker, AWS ECS, ECR, Flask/Node.js, CloudWatch

Skills Demonstrated:

Containerization

Amazon ECR & ECS Fargate Setup

Auto-scaling, Logging with CloudWatch

Bonus: Add ALB for traffic routing.

‚úÖ 3. Infrastructure as Code (IaC) with Terraform on AWS
Project Name: aws-iac-terraform-infra

Overview:

Write Terraform code to provision:

VPC

Subnets

EC2 Instances

S3 Buckets

Security Groups

Tech Stack:

Terraform, AWS

Skills Demonstrated:

IaC with Terraform Modules

AWS Resource Automation

State Management

Best practices like variables.tf, outputs.tf, etc.

Bonus: Use remote backend (S3 + DynamoDB) for state storage.

‚úÖ 4. Monitoring Stack with Prometheus + Grafana on AWS EC2
Project Name: monitoring-prometheus-grafana-aws

Overview:

Deploy Prometheus and Grafana on EC2 (Docker-based setup).

Monitor EC2 instance metrics and expose via node_exporter.

Create Grafana dashboards.

Tech Stack:

Docker, Prometheus, Grafana, EC2, Bash

Skills Demonstrated:

Monitoring setup

Dashboard creation

Exporter usage

Service persistence using Docker volumes

